   BENEFITS-GAP _ Since the 1970s, the gap in wages between skilled
and unskilled workers has widened sharply. But new research shows
the inequality doesn't stop there. Discrepancies in job benefits
and the quality of work life have also grown, pointing to a bigger
chasm than previously recognized. By Peter Passell. (With graphic.)
