<P>
   NY-CHINESE-THEATER (New York) _ For decades, Chinese immigrants
flocked to Chinatown's eight or so Chinese-language movie theaters
because the movies delivered about the only entertainment around
and because the theaters afforded a sense of community and comfort.
But soon, New York City's last Chinese-language theater, the Music
Palace, will take its final bow, its faded three-story structure to
be demolished and replaced by a gleaming office building. By David
W. Chen.
</P>
