<P>
   ILL-HAMAS-SUSPECT (Bridgeview, Ill.) _ The house on Thomas
Street in this suburb 15 miles southwest of Chicago has a red rose
bush growing under the front window, fishing rods leaning against
the door and two boys in Bulls T-shirts shooting baskets in the
drive. But, according to federal authorities, these stock images of
middle-American life are deceiving: this is the home of a man who
has operated secretly as a high-ranking member of the Islamic
terrorist organization Hamas, they say. By David Johnston.
</P>
