<HEADLINE>
ELSTER'S FAN-APPRECIATION SITE PROMISES PLENTY OF INTERACTION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By TOMMY CUMMINGS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   While Rangers shortstop Kevin Elster is on the 15-day disabled
list, Elster's personal manager tries not to give him much to think
about.
</P>
<P>
   Don't hold him to this, but Wayne Hanks has an idea that Elster
``might'' be putting some thought into his Fan-Appreciation
Entertainment Site (www.elster.com) during the down time.
</P>
<P>
   ``I try to give him some time to himself at this time, but I'm
sure (development of the Web site) is the kind of stuff he's
thinking about,'' said Hanks, who works with Elster in ventures
outside of major-league baseball.
</P>
<P>
   Elster, who deferred comments about the site to his
representatives, is recovering from a dislocated shoulder he
sustained June 1.
</P>
<P>
   Web sites are probably not his greatest concern, but if Elster
is putting thought into his site, it appears to be a lot to think
about. Elster.com is loaded with the promise of interaction not
normally seen on most personal Web sites, especially any associated
with the Rangers.
</P>
<P>
   Elster.com has several user-friendly games in the works. If
everything goes as designer Rick Gardner plans, the games will not
require the plug-in software usually associated with online
interaction.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the features on Elster.com are scheduled to be activated
gradually and during stages, said Gardner of Gardner Graphics in
Hollywood, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   ``The site's going to be in ongoing development for the next
month to six weeks,'' Gardner said.
</P>
<P>
   Elster and his wife, Kimberlee Drake, actively suggested game
concepts to Gardner, whose job is to develop them.
</P>
<P>
   Gardner's trivia game on Elster promises long-lasting fun.
Gardner said he has designed the database to remember the score of
each player's performance from visit to visit.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the interactive games, Elster.com also promises
chat sessions and news updates.
</P>
<P>
   Features up and running include a ticker update on Elster, a
photo gallery, a baseball forum and cyber postcards. The site also
includes an index of links to other Elster fan pages. Many of the
site's pages have sizable graphics, so be prepared for long
downloads.
</P>
<P>
   Gardner said he has not worked on a sports site before.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a lot more fun and more cool than I thought it would
be,'' he said. &QL; 
BYTES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The WNBA, hey: WNBA.com, official site for the Women's NBA, is
providing live in-game box scores and play-by-play, and live audio
of every regular-season game. GameStats Live has real-time score
updates, box scores and statistics. The Audio League Pass costs $8
per game with a free trial offer expiring Thursday. The site has
several other interactive features, including chat sessions, user
polls, Fan Forums, quizzes, contests and player mailboxes.
</P>
<P>
   Industry news: Users spend one more minute per day on CNNSI.com
than on ``Playboy'' magazine's site. Those are the findings of a
study conducted in April by Media Matrix, the Nielsen ratings of
Web use. CNNSI.com had the highest daily average minutes (11.7)
among all major news, information and entertainment sites.
``Playboy'' was second with 10.3. Hotmail.com, a free E-mail site,
was third with 8.5, and ESPN SportsZone was fourth with 8.2 ...
Real Networks Inc. won a big audience with its site
(www.real.com/worldcup) that features dozens of multimedia
cybercast sources for the World Cup '98 soccer championships ...If
you're not a Generation X member and are annoyed by skateboarders,
skip this item. ESPN Internet Group is asking online users to vote
on whether downhill skateboarding and freestyle motocross belong in
ESPN's 1999 X games. ESPN is using the X Games' official site
(xgames.espn.com) to help shape next year's Games. During the
telecast of the Games in San Diego beginning Friday, viewers will
be shown video of the two new sports and be encouraged to vote
online. Users also be able to vote on the Game's top athletes and
the theme song.
</P>
<P>
   Chat highlights: New York Yankees outfielder Tim Raines, noon
Tuesday, Bigleaguers.com ... Former New York Cosmos goalkeeper Shep
Messing, 6 p.m. tomorrow, CBS SportsLine ... Boston Celtics general
manager Chris Wallace, noon tomorrow, ESPN SportsZone.
</P>
</TEXT>
