talented and has won more races in the last three years than any
driver in NASCAR. But many drivers don't like him and legions of
NASCAR fans despise him. When Jeff Gordon was pushed into the wall
in Richmond last week, thousands of fans stood and cheered at his
misery. The question: Why? (Levine, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
