<SLUG> BC-SOC-WORLDCUP-BELGIUMNETHERLANDS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BELGIUM'S DUTCH TREAT IS A STALEMATE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By FRANK DELL'APA  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAINT-DENIS, France _ Belgium coach George Leekens decided not
to start playmaker Enzo Scifo against the Netherlands last night.
Predictably, Belgium made few plays. In fact, the Belgians arrived
at Stade de France in a mood to destroy, not create.
</P>
<P>
   The strategy paid off as they held the Dutch to a 0-0 draw. The
result was greeted as a victory by Belgian fans but the defensive
nature of this Low Country produced the low point of this World
Cup.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm pleased with the result,'' Leekens said. ``We tried to
play offensively but they pushed us. Now, we need to win the second
game, against Mexico, for me the most important game.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dutch attacked and pressured, and had two shots cleared off
the line by Belgium's substitute defender Eric Deflandre. But by
the end, they were frustrated, and striker Patrick Kluivert paid
for it by being ejected in the 81st minute.
</P>
<P>
   Though the Belgians were in a defensive mood, they were
dangerous in counterattack. Danny Boffin and Marc Wilmots created
chances, and Luis Oliveira and Lakonda Mpenza seemed capable of
finishing. Luc Nilis missed their best chance, inches high 12
minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Bergkamp and Boudewijn Zenden entered for Jimmy Floyd
Hasselbaink and Clarence Seedorf in the 20th minute of the half.
</P>
<P>
   Zenden and Bergkamp nearly combined seven minutes after they
entered. Kluivert flicked on to Zenden, who pulled a pass back, but
Bergkamp left-footed over the net from 10 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Kluivert was ejected for a foul on Lorenzo Staelens in the 26th
minute. Kluivert and Staelens clashed, and Kluivert refused a
handshake with Staelens, who responded with a derogatory but soft
shove. Kluivert became more animated and elbowed Staelens, who went
down.
</P>
<P>
   Referee Pierluigi Collina consulted with a linesman and
red-carded Kluivert, who will miss Saturday's match against South
Korea in Marseille and the June 25 meeting with Mexico in St.
Etienne.
</P>
<P>
   ``We created some chances in the first 35 minutes but we didn't
have the luck to score a goal,'' Dutch coach Guus Hiddink said.
``We must increase our luck in the last two games.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
