<SLUG> BC-ATL-WATCH-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Time &AMP; a bottle
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- Way back _ when your eyes were infantile and blurry _
dear old Dad saw enough good in you to think one of your
gas-induced smiles was thanks enough.
</P>
<P>
   But by now he's burped you, babied you, berated you, befriended
you and bailed you out so many times that your usual, ``Oh yeah,
thanks'' gifts on Father's Day just won't cut it anymore.
</P>
<P>
   So before you go (last-minute) shopping, think about how he
bottle-fed you, taught you how to make Kool-Aid, counseled you
against drinking and driving and proposed a toast at your wedding.
</P>
<P>
   Then resolve to give something significant in return.
</P>
<P>
   This Father's Day, buy him some time. Or a bottle. Or both.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
